Plug-in name: Dive
Plug-in shortname: dive
Description: An interactive imprecision graph generator for Eva.

Most options of the form '-dive-option-name' and without any parameter
have an opposite with the name '-dive-no-option-name'.

Most options of the form '-option-name' and without any parameter
have an opposite with the name '-no-option-name'.

Options taking a string as argument should preferably be written
-option-name="argument".

***** LIST OF AVAILABLE OPTIONS:

-dive-depth-limit <N>  Build dependencies up to a depth of N.
-dive-from-alarms <f1,...>  Build the graph from the alarms emitted in the
                    given functions. (preferably use
                    -dive-from-alarms="f1,...")
-dive-from-variables <f::v,...>  Build the graph from these local variables.
                    (preferably use -dive-from-variables="f::v,...")
-dive-hide <f::v,...>  Defines the variables which must not be displayed in
                    the graph. The dependencies for these bases are not
                    computed either. (preferably use -dive-hide="f::v,...")
-dive-output-dot <output.dot>  Outputs the built graph in DOT format to the
                    specified file.
-dive-output-json <output.json>  Outputs the built graph in JSON format to
                    the specified.
-dive-unfold <f::v,...>  Defines the composite variables which should be
                    unfolded into individual cells. (preferably use
                    -dive-unfold="f::v,...")

*** DEBUG

-dive-debug <n>     level of debug for plug-in Dive (default to 0)

*** GETTING INFORMATION

-dive-help          help of plug-in Dive
-dive-h             alias for option -dive-help

*** OUTPUT MESSAGES

-dive-log <K_1:file_1,...>  copy log messages from Dive to a file. <K> is a
                    combination of these characters:
                    a: ALL messages (equivalent to 'dfiruw')
                    d: debug       e: user or internal error (same as 'iu')
                    f: feedback    i: internal error
                    r: result      u: user error    w: warning
                    An empty <K> (e.g. ":file.txt") defaults to 'iruw'. One
                    plug-in can output to several files and vice-versa.
                    (preferably use -dive-log="K_1:file_1,...")
-dive-msg-key <k1[,...,kn]>  enables message display for categories
                    <k1>,...,<kn>. Use -dive-msg-key help to get a list of
                    available categories, and * to enable all categories
                    (preferably use -dive-msg-key="k1[,...,kn]")
-dive-verbose <n>   level of verbosity for plug-in Dive (default to 1)
-dive-warn-key <k1[=s1][,...,kn[=sn]]>  set warning status for category <k1>
                    to <s1>,...,<kn> to <sn>. Use -dive-warn-key help to get
                    a list of available categories, and * to enable all
                    categories. Possible statuses are inactive, feedback,
                    warning, error, abort, feedback-once, warning-once,
                    error-once. Defaults to warning. (preferably use
                    -dive-warn-key="k1[=s1][,...,kn[=sn]]")
